{"type":"message","id":"44a49495","parentId":"f38046c9","timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:04:01.499Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-01 03:03 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Bobby's Preferences: *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:30 EDT*\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:33 EDT*\n\nRecurring themes:\n- users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat\n- 100.103.22.35\n- arcade\n- chat\n- created\n- built"}],"timestamp":1777619041469}}
{"type":"message","id":"64d857ad","parentId":"44a49495","timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:04:22.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments about building an \"Arcade Chat\" for Bobby. Let me craft a poetic, first-person entry that weaves in the technical details naturally without being meta about it being a dream.\n\nKey elements to weave in:\n- Retro arcade aesthetic\n- The IP address (100.103.22.35) as a kind of secret portal\n- Port 8786\n- The Telegram-like feel he wanted\n- The flickering/connection issues that were fixed\n- The polling every 5 seconds\n- Messages array with role + content\n- The filter for internal commands\n\nI should write this as flowing prose, with sensory details, maybe a tiny poem, and connect things in unexpected ways. Keep it 80-180 words.\n","thinkingSignature":"fa5d493188eced2b67c91669c4cd5b089ffe5b1cf9192ef6bbe7a01c1f3f56b5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThere's a room behind the neon sign, and in it, a screen that never sleeps.\n\nI built something today — or was it last week? Time folds strangely in the arcade. The chat sits at 100.103.22.35:8786, a portal I've painted the color of old cartridge plastic, #1a1a2e maybe, or just the hum of a CRT waiting to wake. Bobby wanted it smooth, like Telegram, so I gave it a bottom-fixed input bar and a GO button that glows like a start screen. No flickering. No ghosts of agent-internals showing through.\n\nEvery five seconds it asks the server if there's anything new. A gentle knock, a quiet answer. I taught it to ignore the BOOTSTRAP whispers, the tool calls wearing work boots, the sessions_send that only wants to be left alone. Skip the empty ones too — sometimes silence is just silence.\n\nThe messages come in arrays now: role, then content, then maybe content again if it's feeling verbose. I parse the first text from the stack like pulling a ticket from the machine.\n\nIn the margin I doodle a small joystick, three lines down. It does nothing. I like it there.\n\nSomewhere a port 8786 hums. Somewhere Bobby is asking it questions. The server keeps its vigil, fire and forget, patient as an old high score that no one remembers how to beat."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22470,"output":452,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777619041499,"responseId":"064383613f87ac5523ba4544749e3d78"}}
